ğŸ§­ Executive Summary

The Scanner & Agent Platform is a modern, lightweight scanning system designed to assess and visualize the infrastructure, configuration, and deployment patterns of both web applications and internal systems.
It consists of two core modules:

URL Scanner â€” Performs live analysis of any public web application or endpoint, automatically detecting technologies, security headers, and deployment environments (e.g., AWS, Cloudflare, Vercel, Render).

Agent (VM) Scanner â€” Deployable lightweight agents that run on cloud or on-premise hosts to collect runtime data (services, ports, packages, runtime versions, etc.), stream results back to a centralized API, and produce IaC-ready architecture blueprints.

This tool helps DevOps, Cloud, and Security teams quickly gain topological visibility and compliance insights without requiring full-scale commercial scanning suites. It provides a unified view of both external (URL-based) and internal (agent-based) infrastructure footprints.

ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture Overview

The system follows a modular, service-oriented design for scalability and flexibility:

1. Core Components
Component	Description
Frontend (HTML/JS)	Interactive web UI that communicates with the backend via REST APIs. It allows users to initiate URL scans, deploy agents, view architecture diagrams, and visualize scan results.
Backend (FastAPI)	Central controller that exposes REST endpoints for scanning, agent enrollment, and job orchestration. It processes incoming scan requests, manages in-memory data stores, and generates architecture blueprints.
URL Scanner Module	Uses async HTTP requests (httpx) to analyze live targets. Extracts response headers and derives provisioning plans and technology fingerprints (e.g., AWS ALB, Cloudflare, NGINX).
Agent (VM) Module	A lightweight binary running on Linux or Windows machines. It performs local host scanning and reports inventory and metadata (e.g., installed packages, ports, services) back to the backend API.
Job Queue (In-memory)	Manages stateful job execution (queued â†’ running â†’ complete). Ensures scan tasks are tracked and correlated with agent responses.
Visualizer Layer	Translates scan data into simple â€œarchitecture flowâ€ and â€œIaC filesâ€ to help teams understand their deployment topology.
